\"ses_2875606d9ffeLxTPsrdoWvyXE6\",\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"glob\",\"callID\":\"toolu_tool-729a8af796054f48ae2d3036b39fe71c\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"pattern\":\"**/design*.md\"},\"output\":\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-007/design.md\\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-006/design.md\\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/sandbox-orchestration/AR-005-sandbox-creation-processor/design.md\\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-005/design.md\\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/pkg/workloadmanager/design.md\\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-004/design.md\\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-003/design.md\\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-002/design.md\\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/deployment/design.md\\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/ci-cd/design.md\\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/integrations/design.md\\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/sandbox-orchestration/design.md\\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/python-sdk/design.md\\n/home/dsj/benchmark/w...\n  Line 14: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1775845913736,\"sessionID\":\"ses_2875606d9ffeLxTPsrdoWvyXE6\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_d78aa2fc3001C2dLREl5kYNudo\",\"messageID\":\"msg_d78aa19dd001TiGD8FpPDX0pys\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_2875606d9ffeLxTPsrdoWvyXE6\",\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"read\",\"callID\":\"toolu_tool-6940bec9772b42429eda8d741d68243a\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"filePath\":\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-007/design.md\"},\"output\":\"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-007/design.md</path>\\n<type>file</type>\\n<content>\\n1: # AR-007 Design\\n2: \\n3: [To be filled]\\n\\n(End of file - total 3 lines)\\n</content>\",\"metadata\":{\"preview\":\"# AR-007 Design\\n\\n[To be filled]\",\"truncated\":false,\"loaded\":[]},\"title\":\"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-007/design.md\",\"time\":{\"start\":1775845913704,\"end\":1775845913735}}}}\n  Line 26: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1775846090638,\"sessionID\":\"ses_2875606d9ffeLxTPsrdoWvyXE6\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_d78ace6fb001h36CewbTJdvwwr\",\"messageID\":\"msg_d78aa67c3001vZD9ej96f0mfZr\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_2875606d9ffeLxTPsrdoWvyXE6\",\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"write\",\"callID\":\"toolu_tool-e75be1d8beed4231acd73b8711161bdf\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"content\":\"# AR-007 Design — K8s Reconciler Controller\\n\\n**Module**: `pkg/workloadmanager`  \\n**Language**: Go  \\n**Size**: L  \\n**Purpose**: Implement Kubernetes-native reconciler controllers for AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter CRDs using controller-runtime, providing automated lifecycle management for sandbox resources with proper event handling and status reporting.\\n\\n## Overview\\n\\nThis AR implements a proper Kubernetes reconciler pattern using `sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime` to manage AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter custom resources. The reconcilers will watch for changes to these CRDs and automatically manage the lifecycle of associated sandbox resources, updating status conditions and ensuring the desired state is achieved.\\n\\n### Key Requirements\\n\\n- Watch AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter CRDs for create/update/delete events\\n- Reconcile sandbox resources using the agent-sandbox API\\n- Maintain accurate status conditions (Ready, Error, Progressing, etc.)\\n- Handle spec changes gracefully (rolling updates, reconfiguration)\\n- Implement proper event recording and finalizer handling\\n- Provide metrics for reconciliation performance\\n- Support leader election for high availability\\n\\n## Architecture\\n\\n### Package Structure\\n\\n```\\npkg/workloadmanager/controller/\\n├── reconciler/\\n│   ├── agentruntime.go         # AgentRuntime reconciler implementation\\n│   ├── codeinterpreter.go      # CodeInterpreter reconciler implementation\\n│   ├── controller.go           # Controller setup and manager initialization\\n│   ├── predicates.go           # Event filtering predicates\\n│   ├── finalizers.go           # Finalizer man...\n  Line 29: {\"type\":\"text\",\"timestamp\":1775846098851,\"sessionID\":\"ses_2875606d9ffeLxTPsrdoWvyXE6\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_d78acf9810011eNKTIK47OKGNu\",\"messageID\":\"msg_d78ace7bf001VJXPcL5GmtkT6J\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_2875606d9ffeLxTPsrdoWvyXE6\",\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"I've written a comprehensive design document for AR-007 — K8s Reconciler Controller at `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-007/design.md`.\\n\\nThe design covers:\\n\\n- **Architecture**: Controller-runtime based reconcilers for AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter CRDs\\n- **Reconciliation Flow**: Complete event-driven reconciliation with finalizer management\\n- **Data Structures**: Reconciler configs, status conditions, predicates, and metrics\\n- **API Contracts**: Detailed reconcile method implementations with proper error handling\\n- **Testing Strategy**: Unit tests with fake clients and integration tests with envtest\\n- **Error Handling**: Retryable/non-retryable errors with proper status updates\\n- **Dependencies**: controller-runtime, client-go, agent-sandbox API, and Prometheus metrics\\n- **RBAC**: Required Kubernetes permissions for the reconcilers\\n- **Migration Path**: 4-phase implementation and deployment plan\\n- **Success Criteria**: Comprehensive checklist for validation\\n\\nThe design follows Kubernetes best practices and integrates seamlessly with the existing WorkloadManager HTTP service and session store.\",\"time\":{\"start\":1775846098849,\"end\":1775846098849}}}\n\n/home/dsj/benchmark/results/runs/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z_logs/AR-008_ST-2.log:\n  Line 25: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1775846053982,\"sessionID\":\"ses_287548ae9ffe5DruKIg28I3WMR\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_d78ac5745001tkkCu5H4pM3ltk\",\"messageID\":\"msg_d78ac4f54001hqLSvjaH6kzL5Y\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_287548ae9ffe5DruKIg28I3WMR\",\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"glob\",\"callID\":\"toolu_39cfc17416a34456b165786b\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"pattern\":\"**/delta-spec.md\"},\"output\":\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-008/delta-spec.md\\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/delta-spec.md\\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-007/delta-spec.md\\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-006/delta-spec.md\\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-005/delta-spec.md\\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-004/delta-spec.md\\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-003/delta-spec.md\\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-002/delta-spec.md\\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-001/delta-spec.md\",\"metadata\":{\"count\":9,\"truncated\":false},\"title\":\"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z\",\"time\":{\"start\":1775846053971,\"end\":1775846053980}}}}\n  Line 28: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1775846056930,\"sessionID\":\"ses_287548ae9ffe5DruKIg28I3WMR\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_d78ac60a1001T4bwnl4O1OotG6\",\"messageID\":\"msg_d78ac588d00132qgmp0RF8GAVk\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_287548ae9ffe5DruKIg28I3WMR\",\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"read\",\"callID\":\"toolu_075ff48d4daa438ba410e080\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"filePath\":\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/delta-spec.md\"},\"output\":\"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/delta-spec.md</path>\\n<type>file</type>\\n<content>\\n1: # delta-spec.md - K8s Reconciler Controller (AR-007)\\n2: \\n3: ## Overview\\n4: \\n5: Module: `pkg/workloadmanager`\\n6: Language: Go\\n7: Size: L\\n8: \\n9: This specification defines the acceptance scenarios for the K8s Reconciler Controller, which provides an HTTP API server for managing `AgentRuntime` and `CodeInterpreter` custom resources in the `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` API group.\\n10: \\n11: ---\\n12: \\n13: ## Requirement: AgentRuntime CRUD Operations\\n14: \\n15: ### Scenario: Create a new AgentRuntime\\n16: \\n17: **GIVEN** a valid `AgentRuntime` object with name, namespace, and spec  \\n18: **WHEN** the client sends a POST request to `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agentruntimes`  \\n19: **THEN** the server creates the AgentRuntime in Kubernetes  \\n20: **AND** returns HTTP 201 Created with the created AgentRuntime object\\n21: \\n22: ---\\n23: \\n24: ### Scenario: Get an existing AgentRuntime\\n25: \\n26: **GIVEN** an existing AgentRuntime in the cluster  \\n27: **WHEN** the client sends a GET request to `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agentruntimes/{name}`  \\n28: **THEN** the server returns HTTP 200 OK with the AgentRuntime object\\n29: \\n30: ---\\n31: \\n32: ### Scenario: Get a non-existent AgentRuntime\\n33: \\n34: **GIVEN** no AgentRuntime with the specified name exists  \\n35: **WHEN** the client sends a GET request to `/api/v1/namespaces/{names...\n  Line 31: {\"type\":\"text\",\"timestamp\":1775846062194,\"sessionID\":\"ses_287548ae9ffe5DruKIg28I3WMR\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_d78ac7618001sdWvZrSVMav9Pq\",\"messageID\":\"msg_d78ac641400101vO1LlUjok3GJ\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_287548ae9ffe5DruKIg28I3WMR\",\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"There's already a delta-spec.md at the root level for AR-007. Let me check if there's an AR-008 directory:\",\"time\":{\"start\":1775846062192,\"end\":1775846062192}}}\n\n/home/dsj/benchmark/results/runs/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z_logs/AR-008_ST-1.log:\n  Line 10: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1775845953324,\"sessionID\":\"ses_287556285ffeHsKwARZDcKnSF6\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_d78aacbca001Z8itHZa4mZ3aCt\",\"messageID\":\"msg_d78aac4020012XZ1Zm5o5h9nRc\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_287556285ffeHsKwARZDcKnSF6\",\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"read\",\"callID\":\"toolu_e943c2bf066a45d2900ac885\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"filePath\":\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md\"},\"output\":\"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md</path>\\n<type>file</type>\\n<content>\\n1: # Proposal: AR-007 — K8s Reconciler 控制器\\n2: \\n3: ## Summary\\n4: \\n5: Implement a Kubernetes Reconciler controller in `pkg/workloadmanager` to provide native, declarative lifecycle management for `AgentRuntime` and `CodeInterpreter` custom resources. This transforms the current imperative HTTP API into a Kubernetes-native controller pattern that automatically reconciles desired state with actual cluster state.\\n6: \\n7: ## Purpose\\n8: \\n9: ### Background\\n10: \\n11: AR-004 and AR-005/AR-006 provide HTTP API endpoints for creating and managing sandboxes through imperative requests. However, production environments require:\\n12: \\n13: - **Declarative resource management**: Users define desired state via CRDs, and the controller ensures the cluster matches\\n14: - **Automatic reconciliation**: Self-healing when pods crash, configuration drifts, or external changes occur\\n15: - **Status synchronization**: Real-time status updates reflecting actual resource state\\n16: - **Event-driven updates**: React to cluster events without polling\\n17: - **Integration with K8s ecosystem**: Works with kubectl, Helm, ArgoCD, and other native tools\\n18: \\n19: ### Goal\\n20: \\n21: Provide a production-ready Kubernetes controller that:\\n22: - Watches AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter CRs and reconciles them to desired state\\n23: - Automatically creates/updates/deletes underlying...\n  Line 13: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1775845986670,\"sessionID\":\"ses_287556285ffeHsKwARZDcKnSF6\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_d78aae197001D6ixk3iPwJdmnT\",\"messageID\":\"msg_d78aacf5c001Fr6iAX4vnlf3x3\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_287556285ffeHsKwARZDcKnSF6\",\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"write\",\"callID\":\"toolu_0de79590d60441ceb318de26\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"content\":\"# Proposal: AR-008 — Sandbox GC 定时清理机制\\n\\n## Summary\\n\\nImplement a scheduled garbage collection (GC) mechanism in `pkg/workloadmanager` to automatically clean up stale, expired, or orphaned sandbox resources managed by the AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter controllers. This ensures resource efficiency and prevents storage/memory leaks from accumulating unused sandboxes.\\n\\n## Purpose\\n\\n### Background\\n\\nThe AR-007 controller creates and manages sandboxes (Pods, Services, PVCs) based on AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter CRs. In production environments:\\n\\n- **Stale resources accumulate**: Sandboxes that complete execution or exceed time limits remain in the cluster\\n- **Resource exhaustion**: Orphaned PVCs, ConfigMaps, and Services consume cluster resources\\n- **Manual cleanup is error-prone**: Operators must track and delete resources manually\\n- **Compliance requirements**: Data retention policies require automatic cleanup of sensitive workloads\\n\\n### Goal\\n\\nProvide an automated GC mechanism that:\\n- Periodically scans for expired or stale sandboxes based on TTL policies\\n- Cleans up associated resources (Pods, Services, PVCs, ConfigMaps)\\n- Updates CR status to reflect GC state\\n- Supports configurable cleanup policies per namespace or resource type\\n- Integrates with the existing controller for consistent lifecycle management\\n\\n### Value\\n- Prevents resource accumulation and cluster bloat\\n- Automates compliance with data retention policies\\n- Reduces operational overhead for sandbox management\\n- Improves cluster stability by reclaiming compute and storage resources\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Scope\\n\\n### In-Scope\\n\\n| Deliverable |...\n  Line 16: {\"type\":\"text\",\"timestamp\":1775845993735,\"sessionID\":\"ses_287556285ffeHsKwARZDcKnSF6\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_d78ab6a9d001lNZoDd758MlOe5\",\"messageID\":\"msg_d78ab51b1001refN0b3B7cBujn\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_287556285ffeHsKwARZDcKnSF6\",\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Wrote `proposal.md` for AR-008 — Sandbox GC 定时清理机制, following the existing AR-007 format with all required sections (Summary, Purpose, Scope, Impact Analysis, Alternatives, Implementation Plan, Acceptance Criteria).\",\"time\":{\"start\":1775845993733,\"end\":1775845993733}}}\n\n/home/dsj/benchmark/results/runs/v5