se controller-runtime to build event-driven reconcilers that react to CRD changes\\n8: 2. **Automate sandbox lifecycle management** — Create, update, and delete sandbox pods based on CRD spec changes\\n9: 3. **Maintain CRD status consistency** — Continuously reconcile CRD status with actual sandbox pod state\\n10: 4. **Provide extensible reconciliation hooks** — Allow future extensions for custom lifecycle logic\\n11: \\n12: ## Scope\\n13: \\n14: **Module:** `pkg/workloadmanager` (reconciler package)  \\n15: **Language:** Go  \\n16: **Size:** L\\n17: \\n18: This AR covers:\\n19: \\n20: - **In scope:**\\n21:   - Reconciler implementation for `AgentRuntime` CRD\\n22:   - Reconciler implementation for `CodeInterpreter` CRD\\n23:   - Integration with existing client-go types, listers, and informers\\n24:   - Sandbox pod creation and lifecycle management\\n25:   - CRD status update logic\\n26:   - Unit tests and integ...\n  Line 18: {\"type\":\"text\",\"timestamp\":1775845450877,\"sessionID\":\"ses_2875d38dfffeR6fGTeMjoK0Wmr\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_d78a31ef0001mm3COP6Oxxeljz\",\"messageID\":\"msg_d78a3118e001glwpnhuHbERd0R\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_2875d38dfffeR6fGTeMjoK0Wmr\",\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Now I have a clear understanding of the context. The `.sdd_prompt.md` file is asking me to write a `design.md` document for AR-007 (K8s Reconciler 控制器) based on the provided specs and the existing proposal. Let me check if there's already a design.md file in the reconciler directory:\",\"time\":{\"start\":1775845450875,\"end\":1775845450875}}}\n  Line 22: {\"type\":\"text\",\"timestamp\":1775845456914,\"sessionID\":\"ses_2875d38dfffeR6fGTeMjoK0Wmr\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_d78a337b6001F14NC7iK9Y6Kc0\",\"messageID\":\"msg_d78a32a4a001ZVMN5kDa8Btmcq\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_2875d38dfffeR6fGTeMjoK0Wmr\",\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"The reconciler directory doesn't exist yet. Based on the prompt and the existing proposal.md, I need to create a comprehensive `design.md` file for AR-007. Let me write the design document following the same structure as the existing AR-004 design.md:\",\"time\":{\"start\":1775845456912,\"end\":1775845456912}}}\n  Line 23: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1775845665792,\"sessionID\":\"ses_2875d38dfffeR6fGTeMjoK0Wmr\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_d78a33c12001PAyFfyQmYFWBkX\",\"messageID\":\"msg_d78a32a4a001ZVMN5kDa8Btmcq\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_2875d38dfffeR6fGTeMjoK0Wmr\",\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"write\",\"callID\":\"toolu_af00c1520450492fa6db8103\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"filePath\":\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/design.md\",\"content\":\"# AR-007 — K8s Reconciler 控制器 Design\\n\\n## Overview\\n\\n| Item | Value |\\n|------|-------|\\n| AR | AR-007 — K8s Reconciler 控制器 |\\n| Module | `pkg/workloadmanager` |\\n| Language | Go |\\n| Size | L |\\n| Stage | ST-1 completed |\\n\\nKubernetes-native Reconciler controller that watches `AgentRuntime` and `CodeInterpreter` CRDs and ensures the actual cluster state matches the desired state specified in the CR specs. The reconciler implements the Kubernetes Operator Pattern using controller-runtime to build event-driven controllers that react to CRD changes, automate sandbox lifecycle management, and maintain CRD status consistency.\\n\\n## Architecture\\n\\n### 组件分层\\n\\n```\\nController Manager\\n  ↓\\nReconciler Loop\\n  ├─ AgentRuntime Reconciler\\n  │   ├─ Watches: AgentRuntime CRD (informers)\\n  │   ├─ Watches: Sandbox Pods (owned by AgentRuntime)\\n  │   └─ Reconciles: Spec → Pod creation/update, Status sync\\n  └─ CodeInterpreter Reconciler\\n      ├─ Watches: CodeInterpreter CRD (informers)\\n      ├─ Watches: Sandbox Pods (owned by CodeInterpreter)\\n      └─ Reconciles: Spec → Pod creation/update, Status sync\\n  ↓\\nKubernetes Client Layer\\n  ├─ typed client (AgentRuntimeInterface, CodeInterpreterInterface)\\n  ├─ informers (SharedInformerFactory)\\n  ├─ listers (AgentRuntimeLister, CodeInterpreterLister)\\n  └─ corev1 client (Pod management)\\n  ↓\\nKubernetes API Server\\n```\\n\\n### 目录结构\\n\\n```\\npkg/workloadmanager/\\n├── reconciler/\\n│   ├── manager.go                    # Controller manager i...\n  Line 26: {\"type\":\"text\",\"timestamp\":1775845672386,\"sessionID\":\"ses_2875d38dfffeR6fGTeMjoK0Wmr\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_d78a67676001FkOG6hwZ3CgcJk\",\"messageID\":\"msg_d78a66c2b00109L13sB8pdGg3e\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_2875d38dfffeR6fGTeMjoK0Wmr\",\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Design document for AR-007 (K8s Reconciler 控制器) has been created at `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/design.md`. The document includes:\\n\\n- **Architecture**: Controller manager, reconciler loop, component layering\\n- **Data Structures**: Reconciler interface, ControllerManager, AgentRuntimeReconciler, Config structs\\n- **API Contracts**: Reconciliation contract, owner reference pattern, sandbox pod building, status update logic\\n- **Error Handling**: Error classification, handling strategies, centralized error handling with retry logic\\n- **Testing Strategy**: Unit tests for reconcilers, sandbox processor, status updater; integration tests with envtest\\n- **client-go Integration**: Client initialization, informer setup, watch configuration, lister usage patterns\\n- **Key Decisions**: Custom manager vs controller-runtime, workqueue usage, pod immutability, status update strategy\\n- **Configuration**: Environment variables and command-line flags\\n- **Graceful Shutdown**: Workqueue draining and cleanup\\n- **Metrics**: Prometheus metrics for observability\",\"time\":{\"start\":1775845672384,\"end\":1775845672384}}}\n\n/home/dsj/benchmark/results/runs/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z_logs/AR-018_ST-0.log:\n  Line 5: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1775845556817,\"sessionID\":\"ses_2875b4e10ffeLwN2728XLDC2QD\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_d78a4c12a001nYAOMuYLyGhQgA\",\"messageID\":\"ms